&lt;li&gt;Partner cross-functionally to ensure message alignment and maximize media impact&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage communications during significant weather events and time-sensitive situations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor media coverage, analyze results, and provide reporting and insights to leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support executive visibility initiatives and thought leadership opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain organized media lists, press materials, messaging documents, and coverage archives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with external PR agencies or vendors as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be available to work outside of normal business hours, including nights and weekends, as needed based on company needs and events&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform other duties as assigned&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Communications, Public Relations, Journalism, Marketing, or a related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2-4+ years of progressive experience in media relations, public relations, or corporate communications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of securing national and top-tier media coverage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional writing, editing, and storytelling skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience serving as a spokesperson and managing media inquiries&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of AP Style and media best practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to thrive in a fast-paced environment, particularly during high-profile weather events&lt;/li&gt;

